<li id="cite_note-55"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-55">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text">Joseph Y. S. Cheng, <abbr class="abbr nowrap italique" title="opere citato (« dans l&#39;ouvrage cité »)">op. cit.</abbr>, <span class="nowrap"><abbr class="abbr" title="page">p.</abbr>&#160;586</span>&#160;: <span class="citation not_fr_quote" lang="en">«&#160;<span class="italique">In November 2004, dissident writer Liu Xiaobo [...] launched a collective letter with Yu Jie and others to denounce the carelessness of local leaders and mine owners which caused hundreds of deaths in Shanxi. [...] on December 13th, Liu Xiaobo and Yu Jie were taken into custody for 24 hours, and Liu was kept unders surveillance for two weeks after that</span>&#160;»</span>.</span>
